---
const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Who is Speke built for?',
    answer: 'Speke is for modern remote and hybrid teams that need stronger knowledge sharing, faster decisions, and clearer day-to-day alignment.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Is Speke only for teams moving off email?',
    answer: 'No. Speke is built for teams already using tools like Microsoft Teams, chat, and docs, but still missing a single communication layer for context + instant voice.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How does Speke help teams stay in sync?',
    answer: 'Teams write updates in structured channels, jump into voice for quick alignment, and capture outcomes back in the same place so context is never lost.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can we run Speke with our existing stack?',
    answer: 'Yes. Speke is designed to sit alongside your current collaboration tools and tighten communication loops across product, ops, and leadership.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is available today?',
    answer: 'The product already supports text channels, voice rooms, presence indicators, real-time messaging, and organization-level workspace management.'
  }
];
---

<section class="section" id="faq">
  <div class="shell">
    <div class="section-heading reveal">
      <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Questions from remote team leaders</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      {faqs.map((item) => (
        <details class="faq-item reveal">
          <summary>{item.question}</summary>
          <p>{item.answer}</p>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
